b   retrieved  november    palazzo alex october   gaze into the crystal ball – nobel prize predictions transcription and translation scienceblogs retrieved  november    courtney kd corcoran rb engelman ja february  the pik pathway as drug target in human cancer j clin oncol   – pmc   pmid  doijco   wong kk engelman ja cantley lc february  targeting the pik signaling pathway in cancer curr opin genet dev   – pmc   pmid  doijgde   cantley lc may  the phosphoinositide kinase pathway science   – bibcodescic pmid  doiscience   press announcements  fda approves zydelig for three types of blood cancers wwwfdagov archived from the original on  retrieved    songyang z blechner s hoagland n hoekstra mf piwnicaworms h cantley lc november  use of an oriented peptide library to determine the optimal substrates of protein kinases curr biol   – pmid  dois   yaffe mb rittinger k volinia s et al december  the structural basis for phosphopeptide binding specificity cell   – pmid  dois   yaffe mb leparc gg lai j obata t volinia s cantley lc april  a motifbased profile scanning approach for genomewide prediction of signaling pathways nat biotechnol   – pmid  doi   obenauer jc cantley lc yaffe mb july  scansite  proteomewide prediction of cell signaling interactions using short sequence motifs nucleic acids res   – pmc   pmid  doinargkg   turk be huang ll piro et cantley lc july  determination of protease cleavage site motifs using mixturebased oriented peptide libraries nat biotechnol   – pmid  doi   hutti je jarrell et chang jd et al october  a rapid method for determining protein kinase phosphorylation specificity nat methods   – pmid  doinmeth   a b rameh le tolias kf duckworth bc cantley lc november  a new pathway for synthesis of phosphatidylinositolbisphosphate nature   – bibcodenaturr pmid  doi   auger kr carpenter cl cantley lc varticovski l december  phosphatidylinositol kinase and its novel product phosphatidylinositol phosphate are present in saccharomyces cerevisiae j biol 