rmerly a professor in the departments of systems biology and medicine at harvard medical school and the director of cancer research at the beth israel deaconess medical center in boston massachusetts in  he was elected chairman of the board for the hope funds for cancer research contents  biography  research  discovery of pikinase and ptdinsp  use of oriented peptide libraries to determine phosphopeptide binding specificity and protein kinase substrate specificity  discovery of ptdinsp  role of metabolism in cancer  role of pikinase in different cancers  industrial activities  awards honors and media appearances  references  external links biographyedit cantley grew up in west virginia remaining in west virginia at wesleyan college where he graduated summa cum laude in chemistry in  cantley obtained his phd at cornell university in ithaca new york where he worked with gordon hammes on enzyme kinetics using fret to study enzyme conformational changes in  he moved to harvard university for a postdoctoral fellowship under guido guidotti where he discovered that an impurity in commercial preparations of atp vanadate acts as a transition state analog for phosphate hydrolysis in  cantley became assistant professor of biochemistry and molecular biology at harvard being promoted to associate professor in  in  he became a full professor in physiology at tufts university school of medicine in  cantley and colleagues malcolm whitman david kaplan tom roberts and brian schaffhausen made the seminal discovery of the existence of phosphoinositidekinase pik in  cantley moved to harvard medical school as a professor of cell biology and the director of the division of signal transduction at the former beth israel hospital now beth israel deaconess medical center in  cantley became a founding member of the newly formed department of systems biology at harvard medical school in  cantley also became the director of cancer research at the beth israel deaconess medical center he joined th